cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.GT, cs.CL

The paper proposes a general formulation of style transfer as an extension of generative adversarial networks, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also applies this approach to the task of learning to play chess, which involves artificial intelligence and game theory, and thus could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the task of learning to play chess involves analyzing and processing visual information, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing, as it aims to learn to play chess in the style of a specific player, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
